<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11254805-bob-h"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1426548357i/11254805._UX100_CR0,9,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11254805-bob-h">Bob H</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Shouldn&apos;t. The prose is straightforward, the story moves along, the characters fairly compelling. They do tend to speak at length, perhaps because of <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Shouldn't. The prose is straightforward, the story moves along, the characters fairly compelling. They do tend to speak at length, perhaps because of the times, but these soliloquies can be inspiring, esp. Col. Chamberlain's speech to the deserters on the first day of battle.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
